.TH "hvc_iucv_put_chars" 9 "hvc_iucv_put_chars" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hvc_iucv_put_chars \- HVC put_chars operation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hvc_iucv_put_chars
.BI "(uint32_t vtermno "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vtermno" 12
HVC virtual terminal number.
.IP "buf" 12
Pointer to an buffer to read data from
.IP "count" 12
Size of buffer available for reading
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The HVC thread calls this method to write characters to the back-end.
The function calls \fBhvc_iucv_queue\fP to queue terminal data for sending.

Locking:     The method gets called under an \fBirqsave\fP spinlock; and
locks struct hvc_iucv_private->lock.
